5:
I'd advise you to reconsider.
These quests are much more suited 
to your—
10:
I'm, uh, sorry for yelling, but these 
quests aren't gonna cut it.
12:
I've been to the shallows. A million 
times. I come back with hardly 
anything. A few coins and experience 
barely worth mentioning.
15:
I understand what you're saying. But 
the deeper zones are dangerous. 
People who rush in too early don't 
return.
17:
It might not feel like the shallows are 
teaching you much, but your time 
there is acclimating you to the 
Kaleidoscope's shifts and monsters.
20:
I've drawn up some new courses, 
which might help trigger more growth. 
But in the end, there's no rushing—
23: If you don't rush, you get left behind!
37:
Yeah, but he registered at the same 
time as a real prodigy. She's been 
clearing the Kaleidoscope at an 
astounding rate, and he feels like he's 
getting left behind.
39:
They stumble that run fast... But the 
hasty never pause to listen.
42:
I'd even drawn up a few new courses 
for him, to see if any would help him 
get past this bump. But he ran off 
before—
58:
One of our veterans came in with a 
report. There's been indications that 
the midways are about to shift.
60:
We need to put out an alert at once! 
And someone has to get into the 
Kaleidoscope and warn the 
adventurers, stat!
63:
Understood. I'll contact our runners 
and—
68: No need. I'll go the Kaleidoscope!
75:
Someone saw your rookie heading to 
the midways.
87: G-go? Like, to save him? But...
92:
Sounds like a good idea. Folks'll be 
quicker to listen to official staff.
94:
I really shouldn't be sending 
employees into the Kaleidoscope, but 
we're almost out of time!
106: *sigh* Guess I really am a failure.
117:
Heh... The Guild lady even came to 
save me... with a kid and a rabbit…
123: Are you enjoying the view, Sharon?
127:
You know, being up here, feeling the 
wind, takes me back to when I first 
came to Palpebra. I was also young 
and rash and set on making 
something of myself.
129:
...He said he was going to quit 
adventuring.
135:
I saw the old me in that boy. Normal 
kid, surrounded by extraordinary 
people.
136:
It's why we were so eager to prove 
ourselves.
137:
Pride. Hubris. The inability to accept 
that things don't always go our way.
141:
It takes a strong heart to come face-
to-face with your limits, and yet strive 
to grow into something more.
142:
And even if, in the end, you find the 
wall too high to scale, you will still be 
wiser and stronger for the attempt.
146: But of course, you already knew this.
152:
I hope that kid learns the same 
lesson…
159:
It was my pleasure. Come back any 
time.
164:
I, uh, really did mean to give up on 
adventuring, but…
165:
I was eating lunch with my girlfriend, 
and I remembered.
166:
You said you drew up new courses for 
me, right? Mind telling me about 
them?
